Here is the cleaned up text:

Service Cloud Setup is available in Lightning Experience. The Help Center setup flow is the fastest and easiest way to get your help center up and running.

This flow creates a domain, gives your help center a name and path, creates or selects topics to display in your help center, selects article authors, and creates a contact form. If you select Publish my help center in the flow, you opt for immediate publication and your help center is live.

Lightning Knowledge: We turn on Lightning Knowledge if you haven’t already. We create some objects in Lightning Knowledge to get you started, including a Knowledge record type named FAQ, a page layout named Lightning Knowledge FAQ Layout, custom fields Question and Answer, and Permission Set with Authors Permissions Assigned to Users.

Mapping Topics and Data Categories:

Your help center uses topics, data categories, and data category groups to make sure that your customers can find your articles. Data categories and data category groups let you organize your articles so your customer can do less searching.

After completing the setup flow, you have a budding help center that’s ready to be filled with great articles for your customers. Manage Your New Help Center:

View and manage your help center from the Help Center page in Setup. You can create up to 5 help centers with Essentials Edition. Enter Help Center in the Quick Find box, then select Help Center.

Write and Publish Articles:

You can write and manage articles from Knowledge home in Lightning Experience. From the App Launcher, find and open Knowledge. Handle Cases from the Contact Form:

Your contact form creates cases for your team to solve. Create a queue and connect it to your Web-to-Case form using case assignment rules. Show it Off:

Add a link to your help center on your website. You can also set up SEO so that your help center shows up in search results when your customers are looking for answers.
title: Setting Up a Self-Service Help Center with Guided Setup Flow
